id: pm-fuat
title: "CLI ergonomics polish: concise init, help alias collapse, named priorities, package install hints, starter templates, delete dry-run"
description: "Coordinates the remaining pm-5k2w low-severity backlog into one PR. Two specialized sub-agents (help-output-ergonomics, cli-input-ergonomics) own disjoint file sets; coordinator owns shared files (CHANGELOG, docs, completion, contracts), the L10 default-safety Decision, integration, full test/coverage gate, and the manual temp dogfood. Strong theme: reduce agent-facing CLI token cost and remove naive-input footguns. Links pm-5k2w."
type: Plan
status: closed
priority: 2
tags[3]: agent-ux,cli,token-efficiency
